tbeat session** - done (expected)\\n3. **cron:ed2d0b5d** - running ✅ updatedAt 1776194348185 (19:19 UTC)\\n4. **cron:e7885813** - running ✅ updatedAt 1776191108494 (18:25 UTC) - note: this session was started at 18:25:07 UTC, so it's still the same instance\\n5. **telegram:group:-5163901258** - running ✅ updatedAt 1776191432025 (19:10 UTC)\\n6. **telegram:group:direct:6053576134** - done\\n\\nLooking at the full picture, I'm tracking the same critical sessions as the baseline: the two cron jobs for ed2d0b5d and 6f3323ef, plus e7885813 and the telegram group. The Telegram group has refreshed with a new message at 19:10 UTC, so it's no longer stale. I also notice cron:e7885813 was restarted earlier and is now running consistently. The other telegram session ended normally.\\n\\nI'm also seeing several planner subagents and old cron sessions that have completed, along with some failed sessions from the API tests. There are a couple of failed subagents from different agents that are likely still queued, but none of these appear to be new critical failures. The key observation is that the pipeline remains healthy with all primary sessions running as expected.\"\n            },\n            {\n              \"type\": \"text\",\n              \"text\": \"🟡 Orbis-DTLX — 5p Update | 19:21 UTC 14 Apr\\n\\nChanges detected:\\n• No state transitions detected vs. prior baseline (18:26 UTC)\\n• telegram:group:-5163901258 — last activity refreshed at 19:10 UTC (previously stale ⚠️ at 18:15 UTC — now resolved)\\n\\nPipeline: HEALTHY ✅\\n• Active sessions: 3\\n• MCP: stitch ✅ confluence ✅ gitlab ✅\"\n            }\n          ],\n          \"api\": \"anthropic-messages\",\n          \"provider\": \"ahvholding\",\n          \"model\": \"AHV-Holding-DEV\",\n          \"usage\": {\n            \"input\": 28933,\n            \"output\": 549,\n            \"totalTokens\": 43851,\n            \"cacheRead\": 13944,\n            \"cacheWrite\": 425,\n            \"cost\": {\n              \"