)\n3. **cron:e7885813-0446-4101-a171-941c2416848e** (Agent Status to Lead) - running ✅ (updatedAt 1776191108494 = ~19:05 UTC)\n4. **telegram:group:-5163901258** - running ✅ (updatedAt 1776191432025 = ~19:10 UTC)\n\nLooking at the full sessions list, I can see the cron jobs are all active with recent updates, and the Telegram group session is also confirmed running from about 19:10 UTC.\n\nThere's a new cron session that started at 19:24 UTC for the 5p progress report—it's running now as a separate instance. The main session that handles heartbeat monitoring is done, but the cron:ed2d0b5d session still has three active child subagents handling various tasks like the telegram alert and status updates. The QLHV group session and the direct lead session have both ended, though the lead session spawned several subagents that are still processing. Looking at the QLHV monitor session, the three planner subagents are still running from earlier—around 17:11 to 17:18 UTC. I need to compare these against the baseline state to see what's actually changed. The baseline shows the same three cron sessions plus the QLHV group session all running, but I'm noticing the timestamps suggest these subagent sessions are actually much older than the baseline, which means they might have been spawned before it was recorded. I see the baseline included childSessions in its state, so the three planner subagents were already accounted for there. Looking at what actually changed: the cron:e7885813 session updated more recently, the telegram group got reactivated, and there's a new instance of the cron:ed2d0b5d session running with its own child subagents.\n\nComparing the updated timestamps from the baseline at 18:26 UTC to now at 19:24 UTC, all the cron sessions are still running but showing more recent activity, and the telegram group is still active. The actual state hasn't fundamentally changed—no new failures, no blockers. The new cron instance and its subagents appear to be part of a fresh monitoring cycle rather than representing a real state transition.\n\nSo I'm concluding this is a silent exit: everything remains stable, the cron jobs are running as expected, and there are no blockers to report. So all the session states match the baseline — they're all still running as expected. The system health check looks good with 39 total sessions and no failures or blockers, so this qualifies as a silent exit."},{"type":"text","text":"Comparing current state (19:24 UTC) vs. baseline (18:26 UTC):\n\n**Baseline sessions still running:**\n- `cron:ed2d0b5d` ✅ (new cycle, child subagents unchanged)\n- `cron:6f3323ef` ✅\n- `cron:e7885813` ✅\n- `telegram:group:-5163901258` ✅\n\n**No state transitions. No failures. No blockers. Pipeline stable.**\n\nSilent exit — no report sent."}],"api":"anthropic-messages","provider":"ahvholding","model":"AHV-Holding-DEV","usage":{"input":30786,"output":869,"totalTokens":46086,"cacheRead":13944,"cacheWrite":487,"cost":{"total":0}},"stopReason":"stop","timestamp":1776194680648,"responseId":"062dc77a3aff436846e26abdf6e67a60","__openclaw":{"id":"d4146660","seq":5}}]},{"key":"agent:master-orchestrator:cron:6f3323ef-607e-42a0-b946-611913081d31","kind":"other","channel":"webchat","origin":{"provider":"heartbeat"},"label":"Cron: 5p Progress Report - DTLX","displayName":"webchat:g-agent-master-orchestrator-cron-6f3323ef-607e-42a0-b946-611913081d31","deliveryContext":{"channel":"webchat"},"updatedAt":1776194487891,"sessionId":"fb931232-ec48-46d7-97e0-319590dfa62a","model":"AHV-Holding-DEV","contextTokens":200000,"totalTokens":43302,"estimatedCostUsd":0,"status":"running","startedAt":1776188636412,"systemSent":true,"abortedLastRun":false,"lastChannel":"webchat","transcriptPath":"/root/.openclaw/agents/master-orchestrator/sessions/fb931232-ec48-46d7-97e0-319590dfa62a.jsonl","messages":[{"role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"thinking","thinking":"The memory_get returned no content for heartbeat-state.json. The last report (from the cron:e7885813 session at 18:25 UTC) says the baseline was:\n- cron:ed2d0b5d ✅ running\n- cron:6f3323ef ✅ running  \n- cron:e7885813 ✅ running\n- telegram:group:-5163901258 ✅ running (stale at 18:15 UTC)\n\nNow let me compare against the current state at 19:21 UTC:\n\n**Current sessions (from sessions_list):**\n\n1. **cron:6f3323ef** (this session) - running ✅ updatedAt 1776194530055 (~19:22 UTC)\n\n\n2. **main heartbeat session** - done (expected)\n3. **cron:ed2d0b5d** - running ✅ updatedAt 1776194348185 (19:19 UTC)\n4. **cron:e7885813** - running ✅ updatedAt 1776191108494 (18:25 UTC) - note: this session was started at 18:25:07 UTC, so it's still the same instance\n5. **telegram:group:-5163901258** - running ✅ updatedAt 1776191432025 (19:10 UTC)\n6. **telegram:group:direct:6053576134** - done\n\nLooking at the full picture, I'm tracking the same critical sessions as the baseline: the two cron jobs for ed2d0b5d and 6f3323ef, plus e7885813 and the telegram group. The Telegram group has refreshed with a new message at 19:10 UTC, so it's no longer stale. I also notice cron:e7885813 was restarted earlier and is now running consistently. The other telegram session ended normally.\n\nI'm also seeing several planner subagents and old cron sessions that have completed, along with some failed sessions from the API tests. There are a couple of failed subagents from different agents that are likely still queued, but none of these appear to be new critical failures. The key observation is that the pipeline remains healthy with all primary sessions running as expected."},{"type":"text","text":"🟡 Orbis-DTLX — 5p Update | 19:21 UTC 14 Apr\n\nChanges detected:\n• No state transitions detected vs. prior baseline (18:26 UTC)\n• telegram:group:-5163901258 — last activity refreshed at 19:10 UTC (previously stale ⚠️ at 18:15 UTC — now resolved)\n\nPipeline: HEALTHY ✅\n• Active sessions: 3\n• MCP: stitch ✅ confluence ✅ gitlab ✅"}],"api":"anthropic-messages","provider":"ahvholding","model":"AHV