{"type":"message","id":"f5228c5a","parentId":"a327b73b","timestamp":"2026-04-14T19:27:08.417Z","message":{"role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"thinking","thinking":"Now let me analyze the active sessions. The current time is 2026-04-14 19:26 UTC. Let me calculate durations for each active session.\n\nActive sessions (status=running):\n1. **cron:e7885813-0446-4101-a171-941c2416848e** - \"Cron: Agent Status to Lead\" - startedAt 1776194806281 (this cron session itself) - running ~1 minute\n2. **cron:ed2d0b5d-fc56-42eb-a8fc-973a48024df7** - \"Cron: 5p Progress Report\" - startedAt 1776189098508 - running ~94 minutes (started ~17:51 UTC)\n\n\n3. **cron:6f3323ef-607e-42a0-b946-611913081d31** - \"Cron: 5p Progress Report - DTLX\" - startedAt 1776188636412 - running ~100 minutes (started ~17:44 UTC)\n4. **agent:master-orchestrator:main** - heartbeat - status: done (not active)\n5. **agent:master-orchestrator:telegram:group:-5163901258** - \"QLHV Ecosystem group monitoring\" - startedAt 1776163408296 - running ~3 hours 18 minutes (started ~14:03 UTC), though it ended and restarted - status: running\n6. **agent:master-orchestrator:telegram:direct:6053576134** - Lead direct - status: done\n7. **agent:planner:subagent:ba49ac6d-ceff-4a9d-b3b1-7b89afdd88cc** - \"5p-telegram-alert\" - status: done\n\nNow I'm calculating the durations more precisely from 19:26 UTC to figure out how long each session has been active.\n\nThe main cron jobs running are the agent status check that's just started at 19:26 UTC, the QLHV progress report running for about an hour and 35 minutes since 17:51 UTC, the DTLX progress report at about an hour and 42 minutes from 17:44 UTC, and the Telegram group monitoring for around 8 hours since mid-afternoon.\n\nThere's also a subagent from the QLHV monitor that completed its task sending a telegram alert, and I need to send the current status to the lead directly via their direct message session.\n\nLooking at the criteria, there are definitely active sessions beyond just this cron session, so I'll proceed with compiling and sending the report to the lead.","thinkingSignature":"3fdb7b05a9ddf1bd19ce144c4502b67ce5487cf3b18b710370c9d2794da6c093"},{"type":"toolCall","id":"call_function_30vx683ywg5r_1","name":"sessions_send","arguments":{"sessionKey":"agent:master-orchestrator:telegram:direct:6053576134","message":"🌐 Orbis — Agent Status | 19:26 UTC 14 Apr\n\nActive sessions: 4\n• cron:e7885813 (Agent Status → Lead): running — This status report cron — ~1m\n• cron:ed2d0b5d (5p QLHV Progress): running — Ecosystem health monitor — ~1h 35m\n• cron:6f3323ef (5p DTLX Progress): running — DTLX health monitor — ~1h 42m\n• telegram:group:-5163901258 (QLHV Ecosystem): running — Group monitoring / standby — ~3h 18m\n\nPipeline: HEALTHY ✅\n• MCP: stitch ✅ confluence ✅ gitlab ✅\n• No blockers. No revert loopbacks."}}],"api":"anthropic-messages","provider":"ahvholding","model":"AHV-Holding-DEV","usage":{"input":6323,"output":759,"cacheRead":13849,"cacheWrite":314,"totalTokens":21245,"cost":{"input":0,"output":0,"cacheRead":0,"cacheWrite":0,"total":0}},"stopReason":"toolUse","timestamp":1776194813669,"responseId":"062dc7fe780fa0e9535da24352194917"}}
