{"type":"message","id":"68175aba","parentId":"b24b1c37","timestamp":"2026-04-14T19:28:11.483Z","message":{"role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"thinking","thinking":"The session_send is timing out because the target session is likely waiting for an agent response. Let me check if there's another way to communicate. Looking at the tools, there's no direct Telegram send tool. The tts tool is available but that's for text-to-speech.\n\nThe target session `agent:master-orchestrator:telegram:direct:6053576134` is a Telegram direct session for the Lead. Since I can't directly send to it without a response timeout, I should note this in my reply. \n\nThe status report was compiled correctly. Let me respond to the cron session with the outcome.\n\nActually, looking more carefully at the SOUL.md and the cron job design, this cron session is supposed to deliver the report to the Lead via sessions_send. \n\nSince that timed out, I should report the status back to the cron session itself rather than treating this as a silent exit—the task did complete; it just failed to deliver. The other sessions might be stuck waiting for a response or in a loop, but I can't verify that without more information.","thinkingSignature":"83d956146d74c1a9d859d177f5b3fa3695c53977bc9d83ce1139a89598bd4f6a"},{"type":"text","text":"Status report compiled but delivery timed out — target Lead session is awaiting response. Compiling final report for this cron session output:\n\n---\n\n**🌐 Orbis — Agent Status | 19:26 UTC 14 Apr**\n\n**Active sessions: 4**\n- `cron:e7885813` (Agent Status → Lead): **running** — This status report cron — ~1m\n- `cron:ed2d0b5d` (5p QLHV Progress): **running** — Ecosystem health monitor — ~1h 35m\n- `cron:6f3323ef` (5p DTLX Progress): **running** — DTLX health monitor — ~1h 42m\n- `telegram:group:-5163901258` (QLHV Ecosystem): **running** — Group monitoring / standby — ~3h 18m\n\n**Pipeline: HEALTHY ✅** | MCP: stitch ✅ confluence ✅ gitlab ✅ | No blockers. No revert loopbacks